This first clear demonstration of phonon-exciton asymmetry opens doors to next-gen optoelectronics. The material pretends to be a bland cubic citizen but reveals a sophisticated, directionally picky inner life under light. Revolutionary for energy tech and photonics, disorder as deliberate design tool. Schorr’s team calls it “an additional handle for tailoring optoelectronic properties.”"}}}, "rest_id": "2071680515485422002", "source": "<a href="http://twitter.com/download/iphone" rel="nofollow">Twitter for iPhone</a>", "unmention_data": {}, "views": {"count": "33", "state": "EnabledWithCount"}}

